HEADWORD: perfectibility
<hw>perfectibility</hw></mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <def>The capability of becoming perfect; <as>as, he
believes in the ultimate <ex>perfectability</ex> of man</as>; -- usually
spelled <ex>perfectibility</ex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>perfected</ent>⟦br⟧

